The paper deals with the Voronoi diagram, a fundamental geometric object in computational geometry, which is a subfield of computer science. The paper also discusses stability properties of Voronoi diagrams, which is a topic in computational geometry and numerical analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves certain topological properties of Voronoi cells, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MG (Mathematical Software). The paper also involves certain conditions on the unit sphere of the normed space, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper involves certain algorithms and data structures related to Voronoi diagrams, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
